Europe's 'coalition of the willing' still seeks US backing on Ukraine
description: Meeting by videoconference in Paris on Thursday, European leaders and Ukraine's Volodymyr Zelensky hoped for Donald Trump's approval after their promise to offer Kyiv 'security guarantees' should hostilities cease. While no longer openly opposed to this, the US president hesitated.

headline: US economy takes a new hit with too few jobs created in August
description: Only 22,000 jobs were created in the US last month, less than a third of what's required to keep up with population growth. The statistic paves the way for the interest rate cuts sought by Donald Trump, but also raises doubts about his administration's economic policy.

headline: Paris Design Week: A 15th edition marked by abundance
description: Some 375 locations across the French capital are hosting, free of charge from September 4 to 13, the very best in contemporary design. From Aude Franjou's textile coral installation to Hugo Falaise's embroidered furniture, here is our selection of must-see works.

headline: 'Dear Salman Rushdie…': Isabelle Adjani's stand against religious fundamentalism
description: 'Adjani, The Famous Stranger' (4/6). After Iran issued a fatwa against the British writer in 1989, the French actress used the César Awards ceremony to show her support for the author of 'The Satanic Verses.' She was one of the few in the film industry to take such a stand.

headline: Giorgio Armani, one of the makers of modern fashion, is dead
description: Creator, designer and stylist, he made the tailored suit into a status symbol. Armani, who reigned for more than 40 years over a veritable empire, died on Thursday, September 4, at the age of 91, his fashion house confirmed.

description: The recipe for this comforting pastry, enjoyed as a snack or at breakfast? Croissant dough, vanilla custard and chocolate chips. Here is our selection of bakeries offering the best versions.
